<subSubSection id="A7C4ECB9A63611C132A09C03154E2D20" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="19EE6F907F56EDA5D34A7F871099263A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F438C063DA99779D2BC8F468F71FDE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining annual herb, young stems glabrous, older stems setose. Leaves petiolate, 4-9 
<normalizedToken id="422C3F57B49C0D88AB196974E9E1BCDC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 cm, narrowly (to broadly) deltoid, base sagittate to hastate, auricles acute to obtuse, glabrous, abaxially paler; petioles 2-7.5 cm. Inflorescence of 1(-2)-flowered axillary, pedunculate cyme; peduncles 0.5-3.5 cm; bracteoles 8-15 
